The paper deals with a mathematical analysis of a heat diffusion process, which has applications in information theory (cs.IT), graph theory and algorithms (cs.DS), communication complexity (cs.CC), and combinatorics (cs.DM). The paper also uses techniques from probability theory and convex geometry, which are relevant to several subfields of computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT and cs.DS, followed by cs.CC, cs.DM, and cs.SI.
